<!-- wp:maysternya/text-block {"content":"Our interpretation of Chekhov's masterpiece strips away the trappings of period drama to reveal the timeless human longing at its core. Three sisters — Olga, Masha, and Irina — dream of escaping their provincial existence for the promise of Moscow, but find themselves trapped in a web of unfulfilled desires, failed relationships, and the relentless passage of time.\n\nThis production has been hailed as one of the most innovative Chekhov interpretations to emerge from Ukrainian theater in recent decades. The minimalist staging and powerful ensemble work create an intimate experience that draws audiences into the sisters' emotional landscape.","columns":1,"width":"full","alignment":"left"} /-->

